Charity Membership & Donation Management System (low budget project)
Project Architecture & Development Plan
1. Project Objective
Build a web-based application for a charity organization to manage members, monthly membership payments, occasional donations, challan generation, payment proof uploads, admin approvals, dashboards, reports, and notifications. 
The system will replace Excel-based tracking and support desktop, mobile browsers, and Progressive Web App (PWA) installation. 
The project must remain budget-friendly, simple, and scalable for future enhancements.
2. Target Users
Super Admins (Developers)
- Full system, server, database, and configuration access.

Admins (Max 5)
- Manage members, approve payments, create campaigns, export reports, post notifications.

Members
- View profile, create challans, upload proofs, view history, receive notifications.
3. Core Modules
Authentication (JWT, role-based)
Member Management
Payments & Challans
Proof Upload
Notifications (In‑App)
Dashboards (Admin & Member)
Reports & Exports
Excel Import
PWA Support
4. Invitation & Registration Flow
Admins invite users using phone number or email.
System generates an Invite Code.
New user enters Invite Code + Phone/Email.
If matched, user proceeds to registration form.
User fills username, password, address, etc.
Member ID is assigned by Admin.
System suggests next sequential Member ID based on last entry.
5. Challan Logic
Monthly Challans:
- User generates for unpaid months only.
- Fixed monthly amount.

Occasional Donations:
- Admin creates campaign.
- Reflected on all member dashboards.
- User can participate and generate challan.

Status Flow:
Generated → Proof Uploaded → Pending → Approved/Rejected
6. Technology Stack (Budget Friendly)
Frontend: Vue.js (Responsive + PWA)
Backend: FastAPI or Flask
Database: MongoDB or PostgreSQL (Self Hosted)
Storage: Local → Cloud Later
Hosting: VPS Linux Server
Version Control: GitHub
7. Security & Best Practices
Password hashing (bcrypt)
JWT expiration
Role Based Access Control
File validation & size limits
HTTPS only
Audit logs
Database indexing
Weekly backups
Error logging
8. Collaboration Workflow
GitHub Branches:
main – Production
dev – Testing
feature/* – New features
hotfix/* – Urgent fixes

Task Division:
Developer A – Backend, APIs, DB
Developer B – Frontend, UI, PWA
9. Infrastructure Cost (Approx 2 Years)
Domain: ~$30
VPS Hosting: ~$300
SSL: Free
Database: Free (Self Hosted)
Storage: Included
Estimated Total: ~$330
10. Future Enhancements
Email/SMS notifications
Payment gateway
Cloud storage
Multi-language support
Advanced analytics
Mobile native apps
Multi‑organization support
11. Backup Strategy
Weekly database and file backups.
Monthly restore testing.
Later: automated daily backups.
12. Guiding Principle
Keep the system simple, modular, permission‑controlled, and scalable without over‑engineering.
This plan provides a clear roadmap for developing the Charity Membership & Donation Management System while adhering to budget constraints and ensuring scalability for future growth.